        "desc": "Even the most tired and cynical would be awed by the sight of this cavern. The\ncold, dark reality of Moria seems to be suspended here, as if this chamber,\nalone, existed in a different and more tranquil time. The walls, the ceiling,\nand even the floor, sparkle brightly, in even the faintest trace of light,\nsweeping the observer into a world of fantastic images. But all too soon, the\nwondrous luminosity gives way, once more, to dreary, grey, granite walls, as\nAzaghal's Way stretches east and west, and a smaller road slopes gently away to\nthe south.\n",
