        "desc": "The faint, distant thundering of water can be heard here, as you stand at the\nthe top of a long winding staircase. It is impossible to see how far below you\nthe stairs continue, and it is quite tempting to reach for one of the loose\nstones which are scattered around, and drop it to plumb these depths. It seems\nimpossible to fight off a wave of vertigo when contemplating this drop,\nespecially considering that there is no handrail here, and that each tread of\nthe stair is perilously worn and chipped with use.\n",
